<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="188" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1837,1970]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1837,1862]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Members of this group can be recognized by (
<number box="[834,846,1838,1862]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="1.0">1</number>
) shape of the tibial apophysis: wide, with sharply pointed tip directed dorsally, (
<number box="[497,512,1874,1898]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="2.0">2</number>
) S-shaped diagonal course of seminal duct, (
<number box="[1035,1049,1874,1898]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="3.0">3</number>
) short and wide embolus starting from 
<number box="[213,269,1910,1934]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="9.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="9.0">9–10</number>
o’clock, (
<number box="[385,400,1910,1934]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="4.0">4</number>
) epigyne lacking septum and (
<number box="[751,765,1909,1934]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="5.0">5</number>
) small outgrowths (
<emphasis box="[995,1029,1910,1933]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">Op</emphasis>
) of lateral pockets of epigyne (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 19" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1311,1334]" captionTargetBox="[161,1422,193,1290]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[161,1426,193,1291]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 19. Epigyne of Berlandina ubsunurica (10 – 12), epigyne and habitus of B. nenilini (13 – 16) and B. hui (17 – 19). 10 – 11, 13, 15, 17 epigyne, ventral; 12, 14, 18 epigyne, dorsal; 16, 19 habitus. Abbreviation: Op outgrowths of lateral pocket." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/249734/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">Figs 12, 15, 18</figureCitation>
, 47).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
